description: Intel® MPI Library is a multifabric message-passing library that implements the open-source MPICH specification. Use the library to create, maintain, and test advanced, complex applications that perform better on HPC clusters based on Intel® processors. Develop applications that can run on multiple cluster interconnects chosen by the user at run time. Quickly deliver maximum end-user performance without having to change the software or operating environment. Achieve the best latency, bandwidth, and scalability through automatic tuning for the latest Intel® platforms. Reduce the time to market by linking to one library and deploying on the latest optimized fabrics.
summary: Package includes linux-x64 MPI SDK package
